1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 tin Tinned Cherry Tomatoes
100 g Diced Bacon
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Cream
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Pumpkin, Sundried Tomato & Feta Ravioloni
1 drizzle olive oil

• Boil the kettle.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 6-7 minutes.

• Add tinned cherry tomatoes and Nan’s special seasoning and cook until softened, 5 minutes.
• Add baby leaves and stir until just wilted, 1 minute

• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water. Simmer pumpkin, sundried tomato & feta ravioloni over medium-low heat, until ‘al dente’, 3 minutes.
• Using a slotted spoon, transfer ravioloni to the frying pan of sauce and toss to combine.
• Add cream (see ingredients) and half the grated Parmesan cheese to the sauce and stir to combine. Remove pan from heat. Season with salt and
pepper to taste.

• Divide rustic bacon and pumpkin ravioloni between plates.
• Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese to serve. Enjoy!